{"id":"math140-lineval-cr002","cid":"MATH 140","topic":"Functions Cost Revenue Profit","subtopic":"Evaluating cost and revenue functions","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"If revenue is R(x) = {m}x + {b} and cost is C(x) = {m2}x + {b2}, find profit P({x_val}) = R({x_val}) - C({x_val}).","params":{"m":{"type":"int","min":20,"max":60},"b":{"type":"int","min":0,"max":100},"m2":{"type":"int","min":10,"max":30},"b2":{"type":"int","min":100,"max":400},"x_val":{"type":"int","min":5,"max":20}},"answer_expr":"lineval","steps":["P(x) = R(x) - C(x) = ({m} - {m2})x + ({b} - {b2}).","P({x_val}) = {m_times_x} + {b} — you get the idea: compute R({x_val}) - C({x_val})."],"tags":["business-calculus","profit","revenue","cost"]}
